      <div type="transcription" xml:id="transcription_aad_0106" xml:lang="en">
        <div type="letter">
        <pb facs="https://iiif.acdh.oeaw.ac.at/aad/aad_00351/" ed="1r" type="sheet"/>
          <div type="letter_message" hand="#type_black_auden">
            <opener>
              <dateline>
                <seg hand="#print_black_auden">
                  <placeName>
                    <address xml:lang="de">
                      <lb/><rs type="place" ref="#amp_place_id_2">3062 KIRCHSTETTEN
                      <lb/>BEZ. ST. PÖLTEN
                      <lb/>HINTERHOLZ 6
                      <lb/>N.-Ö., <foreign xml:lang="en">AUSTRIA</foreign></rs>
                    </address>
                  </placeName>
                </seg>
                <date>
                  <lb/>July I6th,I97I
                </date>
              </dateline>
              <salute>
                <lb/><space quantity="13" unit="char"/>Dear <rs type="person" ref="#amp_person_137">Dr Kraus</rs>:
              </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>
              <lb/><space quantity="6" unit="char"/>Many thanks for your letter. Could you let me know
              <lb/>two things.
              <seg>
                <lb/><space quantity="2" unit="char"/>I)About how many pages is the <rs type="lit_work" ref="#lit_work_id_67" ana="#ana_106">volume</rs> to contain?
              </seg>
              <seg>
                <lb/><space quantity="2" unit="char"/>2) You speak of <hi rend="underline" hand="#type_black_auden"><foreign xml:lang="de">Manuskripten</foreign></hi>. Does this <del rend="overtyped" hand="#type_black_auden">eman</del> mean that
                <lb/><space quantity="5" unit="char"/>you only wnat poems which have not been published in
                <lb/><space quantity="4" unit="char"/>English in book form?
              </seg>
            </p>
            <closer>
              <salute>
                <lb/><space quantity="23" unit="char"/>Yours sincerely
              </salute>
              <signed hand="#hand_blue_auden">
                <lb/><rs type="person" ref="#amp_person_1">W.H<unclear>-</unclear>Auden</rs>
              </signed>
              <signed>
                <lb/><space/><rs type="person" ref="#amp_person_1">W.H.Auden</rs>
              </signed>
            </closer>
          </div>
          <div hand="#hand_gray_unident_0106">
            <ab>
              <lb/>200 -2<unclear>5</unclear>0
            </ab>
            <ab>
              <lb/>60 -<unclear>12</unclear>0 <unclear>E</unclear><gap reason="illegible" atLeast="2" atMost="3" unit="char"/>l
              <lb/><unclear>T</unclear>e<unclear>xt</unclear>
            </ab>
          </div>
